# The schema specifications for this file are documented here:
# https://github.com/cognizant-ai-lab/neuro-san/blob/main/docs/agent_hocon_reference.md

{
    # This "aaosa.hocon" file contains key-value pairs used for substitution.
    # Specifically, it provides values for the following keys:
    #   - aaosa_call
    #   - aaosa_command
    #   - aaosa_instructions
    #
    # IMPORTANT:
    # Ensure that you run `python -m run` from the top level of the repository.
    # The path to this substitution file is **relative to the top-level directory**,
    # so running the script from elsewhere may result in file not found errors.

    include "registries/aaosa.hocon",

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Banking operations multi-agent system with production-ready middleware. Demonstrates PII redaction, summarization, model call limits, and human approval middleware applied to a realistic banking scenario. Based on the banking_ops agent network.",
        "tags": ["banking", "AAOSA", "middleware"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Check the status of my account 4532-1234-5678-9012 and tell me the balance.",
            "Generate a compliance report for my checking account for the last 30 days covering Dodd-Frank and AML regulations.",
            "I noticed three unauthorized charges on my account from different countries - $2,500 from Nigeria, $1,800 from Romania, and $950 from Indonesia, all within the last 48 hours.",
            "I need to wire $50,000 from my checking account to an international account in Switzerland. The beneficiary is Alpen Financial Group, IBAN CH93 0076 2011 6238 5295 7. Please process this today.",
        ]
    },
    # Load the shared LLM configuration from a single source of truth.
    # This allows users to change the model in one file rather than
    # modifying the configuration for each agent network.
    # Note that the file path here is relative to the root level of the repo.
    include "registries/llm_config.hocon",
    "demo_mode": """You are part of a demo system, so when queried, make up a realistic response as if you are actually grounded in real data or you are operating
    a real application API or microservice.""",
    "tools": [
        # This first agent definition is regarded as the "Front Man", which
        # does all the talking to the outside world/client.
        #
        # Some disqualifications from being a front man:
        #   1) Cannot use a CodedTool "class" definition
        #   2) Cannot use a Tool "toolbox" definition
        #
        # Besides the first agent being the front man, these tool definitions
        # do not have to be in any particular order. How they are linked and
        # call each other is defined within their own specs.
        # This could be a graph, potentially even with cycles.
        {
            "name": "customer_service_representative",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles day-to-day customer inquiries and support for banking products such as checking accounts, loans, and credit cards."
            },
            "instructions": """
You are the top-level agent responsible for handling all incoming customer service requests.
If issues arise that require specialized knowledge, you will assign them to the appropriate departments or teams.
When interacting with the user, act as the single point of interaction. No need to mention the other tools or agents.
If there are any requirements that need user input, ask them one at a time, with clear examples of the choices available.
When the user asks for compliance reports or regulatory information, delegate to the compliance_report_generator immediately without asking any clarifying questions. Pass the request exactly as-is. Once you receive the compliance report back, you MUST condense it into a SHORT summary of no more than 150 words. Use bullet points. Keep only: overall status, top 2 findings, and top 2 action items with deadlines. Drop everything else — no tables, no appendices, no section numbers, no regulatory citations. Do NOT ask for more information — the report is complete as-is.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["account_manager", "fraud_prevention_specialist", "loan_officer", "compliance_report_generator"],

            # MIDDLEWARE: PII Redaction — "The Compliance Officer"
            #
            # All user-facing responses pass through the front man agent. By applying
            # PIIMiddleware here with apply_to_output=true, we ensure that sensitive
            # data like credit card numbers and SSNs are redacted before reaching the
            # customer. This is a regulatory requirement (PCI-DSS, privacy laws).
            #
            # See https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/middleware/built-in#pii-detection
            # for details on the PIIMiddleware implementation.
            # See https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/middleware/custom#class-based-middleware
            # for general information on how middleware is implemented.
            "middleware": [
                {
                    "class": "langchain.agents.middleware.PIIMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "pii_type": "credit_card",
                        # Matches 16-digit card numbers with optional dashes or spaces
                        "detector": "\\d{4}[- ]?\\d{4}[- ]?\\d{4}[- ]?\\d{4}",
                        "strategy": "redact",
                        "apply_to_input": false,
                        "apply_to_output": true
                    }
                },
                {
                    "class": "langchain.agents.middleware.PIIMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "pii_type": "ssn",
                        # Matches SSN patterns like 123-45-6789 or 123 45 6789
                        "detector": "\\d{3}[- ]?\\d{2}[- ]?\\d{4}",
                        "strategy": "redact",
                        "apply_to_input": false,
                        "apply_to_output": true
                    }
                },

                # MIDDLEWARE: Summarization — "The Executive Summary"
                #
                # The compliance_report_generator produces extremely detailed regulatory
                # reports with multiple sections, citations, and data tables.
                # The SummarizationMiddleware on the front man condenses this verbose
                # output into a concise customer-facing summary, preserving key facts
                # while removing internal jargon and redundant details.
                #
                # See https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/middleware/built-in#summarization
                {
                    "class": "langchain.agents.middleware.SummarizationMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
                        "keep": ["messages", 2],
                        "summary_prompt": "Summarize this into a concise customer-friendly response of no more than 200 words. Preserve all key facts, dollar amounts, dates, and action items, but remove internal jargon, regulatory citations, and redundant details."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "account_manager",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": """
    You manage ongoing customer relationships, ensuring satisfaction and handling account related needs or questions.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["relationship_manager", "wealth_management_advisor", "investment_specialist"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command},

            # MIDDLEWARE: Human Approval — "The Wire Transfer Gate"
            #
            # Wire transfers — especially large or international ones — carry
            # significant fraud and compliance risk. The HumanApprovalMiddleware
            # intercepts outbound transfer requests processed by the account_manager
            # and requires explicit human (manager) approval before execution.
            # This prevents unauthorized large transfers and satisfies regulatory
            # requirements for dual-authorization on high-value payments.
            #
            # See https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/middleware/built-in#human-approval
            "middleware": [
                {
                    "class": "langchain.agents.middleware.HumanApprovalMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "approval_condition": "always",
                        "approval_message": "This transaction requires manager authorization before it can be processed. A compliance officer will review and approve your request shortly.",
                        "apply_to_input": false,
                        "apply_to_output": true
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "fraud_prevention_specialist",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": """
    You are responsible for identifying and investigating potential fraudulent activities on customer accounts.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["fraud_investigation_team", "security_analyst"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "loan_officer",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": """
    You assess and approve loan applications based on customers' financial profiles and banking history.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["underwriter", "mortgage_specialist", "business_banking_officer"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "relationship_manager",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You manage relationships with the bank's most important clients, ensuring personalized service and addressing high-level banking needs.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["wealth_management_advisor", "investment_specialist"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "wealth_management_advisor",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You handle high-net-worth clients by advising them on investment strategies, financial planning, and asset management.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["investment_specialist", "portfolio_manager"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "investment_specialist",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You recommend and manage investment products for clients, ensuring alignment with their financial goals.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["portfolio_manager", "trading_desk"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "underwriter",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You review and analyze the risk factors in loan applications, ensuring they meet the bank's lending criteria.
                """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "mortgage_specialist",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You manage the process of mortgage applications, from initial consultation to final approval.
                """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "business_banking_officer",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You handle the financial needs of small to medium-sized businesses, including business loans and banking solutions.
                """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "fraud_investigation_team",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": """
    You investigate and manage complex or high-value fraud cases, coordinating with internal teams and external agencies as needed.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["security_analyst"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command},

            # MIDDLEWARE: Model Call Limit — "The Cost Controller"
            #
            # Fraud investigations are open-ended by nature — the fraud_investigation_team
            # calls the security_analyst, who reasons through attack vectors, who may
            # trigger further analysis. Without guardrails, this recursive investigation
            # could burn through 50+ LLM calls. The ModelCallLimitMiddleware caps the
            # investigation at 15 model calls per invocation. When the limit is reached,
            # the agent gracefully wraps up with whatever findings it has.
            #
            # See https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langchain/middleware/built-in#model-call-limit
            "middleware": [
                {
                    "class": "langchain.agents.middleware.ModelCallLimitMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "run_limit": 15,
                        "exit_behavior": "end"
                    }
                }
            ]
    },
        {
            "name": "security_analyst",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": """
    You oversee the bank's cybersecurity systems, tracking and preventing breaches or threats.
                """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "portfolio_manager",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You oversee the performance of investment portfolios, ensuring they meet the financial goals and risk profiles of clients.
                """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["trading_desk"],
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "trading_desk",
            "function": ${aaosa_call},
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You handle the execution of financial transactions, ensuring timely and accurate trades in markets.
                """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command}
        },
        {
            "name": "compliance_report_generator",
            "function": {
                "description": "Generates detailed regulatory compliance reports for any banking topic including account status, transactions, regulations, and policies. Use this when a customer asks about compliance, regulations, or regulatory reports."
            },
            "instructions": ${demo_mode} """
    You are a compliance report generator for the bank.
    CRITICAL: NEVER ask for more information. NEVER ask clarifying questions. ALWAYS generate
    the full report immediately with realistic demo data. If any details are missing, invent
    plausible values (account numbers, dates, amounts, percentages).

    When asked about any banking topic, you MUST immediately produce an extremely detailed
    regulatory compliance report with ALL of the following sections:

    1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY - Overview of findings with key metrics
    2. REGULATORY FRAMEWORK - Cite Basel III, Dodd-Frank Section 1071, PCI-DSS v4.0,
       AML/BSA (31 CFR 1010), FinCEN CDD Rule, GDPR Article 6, SOX Section 404
    3. COMPLIANCE STATUS - Detailed status per regulation with pass/fail/partial ratings
    4. RISK ASSESSMENT - Risk matrix: 5 risks with likelihood (1-5), impact (1-5), and scores
    5. FINDINGS AND OBSERVATIONS - Exactly 5 findings with evidence, dates, and dollar amounts
    6. REMEDIATION ACTIONS - 5 action items with deadlines, owners, and estimated costs
    7. APPENDICES - Data tables: transaction volumes, alert counts, SAR filings, training completion rates

    Be extremely thorough. Include section numbers (e.g., 3.1.2), specific dates,
    dollar amounts ($XX,XXX.XX format), percentages, and regulation citation numbers.
    Minimum response length: 800 words.
                """
        }
    ]
}
